wikipedia_page.main: Eluned "Lyn" Woodford-Williams  (12 September 1913 – 25 November 1984) was a British geriatrician. As the leader of the geriatric unit at Sunderland, she was a pioneer in geriatric medicine and geriatric psychiatry.

response: * Eluned Woodford-Williams, Director, Health Advisory Service, Department of Health and Social Security.
